
Learn Docker
Welcome to the Learn Docker repository! This repository serves as a resource for individuals looking to learn Docker. Whether you're new to Docker or looking to deepen
your understanding, this repository aims to provide clear and comprehensive explanations alongside practical examples.

Getting Started
To get started with Docker, follow these steps:

Clone the Repository:
git clone https://github.com/AmTripathiDev/Learn-Docker-Caching-and-Layers-.git

Explore the Dockerfile:
The Dockerfile in this repository demonstrates best practices for creating Docker images. Take a look at the comments within the file to understand each step.

Contents
Dockerfile: This file contains instructions for building the Docker image.
index.js: This is the entry point of the Node.js application.
package.json and package-lock.json: These files list the Node.js dependencies required by the application.
Contributing
Contributions to this repository are welcome! If you have any improvements, suggestions, or new content to add, please feel free to open a pull request.

